The paper discusses a recommendation system for movies, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed approach involves optimizing the prediction algorithm's input parameters, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the cold start problem, which is a common issue in human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the authors use a dataset to evaluate their system, which is a common practice in database systems (cs.DB).
